<%# Accessibility Page %>
<div class="bg-white">
  <%# Hero Section %>
  <div class="relative py-16 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-5xl md:text-6xl">
          Accessibility Statement
        </h1>
        <p class="mt-4 max-w-2xl mx-auto text-xl text-gray-500">
          Last updated: March 20, 2024
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <%# Content Section %>
  <div class="relative py-16 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="relative px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose prose-lg prose-indigo mx-auto">
        <h2>Our Commitment</h2>
        <p>
          We are committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.
        </p>
        <h2>Conformance Status</h2>
        <p>
          The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) defines requirements for designers and developers to improve accessibility for people with disabilities. It defines three levels of conformance: Level A, Level AA, and Level AAA.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our website strives to conform to WCAG 2.1 level AA standards. We monitor the website regularly to maintain this and are working to remedy any issues that may arise.
        </p>
        <h2>Accessibility Features</h2>
        <div class="mt-6">
          <h3>Navigation</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Clear and consistent navigation structure</li>
            <li>Skip to main content link</li>
            <li>Descriptive page titles</li>
            <li>Logical heading hierarchy</li>
            <li>Keyboard accessible menus</li>
          </ul>
          <h3>Content</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Alt text for images</li>
            <li>Proper color contrast</li>
            <li>Resizable text without loss of functionality</li>
            <li>Clear link text (no "click here")</li>
            <li>Consistent layout and styling</li>
          </ul>
          <h3>Forms</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Clear labels for form controls</li>
            <li>Error messages are clearly identified</li>
            <li>Required fields are clearly marked</li>
            <li>Form validation feedback</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <h2>Assistive Technology</h2>
        <p>
          Our website is designed to be compatible with the following assistive technologies:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Screen readers (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)</li>
          <li>Screen magnification software</li>
          <li>Speech recognition software</li>
          <li>Keyboard-only navigation</li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Known Issues</h2>
        <p>
          While we strive to ensure accessibility across our entire website, there may be some areas that require improvement. We are actively working to identify and remedy any accessibility issues.
        </p>
        <div class="bg-yellow-50 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-yellow-900">Current Limitations</h3>
          <ul class="mt-2 text-yellow-700">
            <li>Some older PDF documents may not be fully accessible</li>
            <li>Some third-party content may not meet accessibility standards</li>
            <li>Legacy content may require updates to meet current standards</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <h2>Feedback</h2>
        <p>
          We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of our website. If you experience any accessibility barriers or have suggestions for improvement, please contact us:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>By email: accessibility@example.com</li>
          <li>By visiting this page on our website: <%= link_to "Contact Us", new_contact_inquiry_path, class: "text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-500" %></li>
        </ul>
        <h2>Additional Resources</h2>
        <p>
          For more information about web accessibility, we recommend the following resources:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/" class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-500">W3C Web Accessibility Initiative (WAI)</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/" class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-500">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/fundamentals/accessibility-intro/" class="text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-500">Introduction to Web Accessibility</a></li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bg-indigo-50 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-indigo-900">Our Ongoing Commitment</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-indigo-700">
            We are committed to maintaining and improving the accessibility of our website. We regularly review our site for accessibility issues and work to implement improvements based on user feedback and evolving accessibility standards.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>